  "articleSummary": "## Summary\n\n**Main Argument:** Local developer machines have replace production systems as the primary security attack surface—\"your laptop is a credential warehouse with a keyboard.\" The old model where local development is safe and production is dangerous is fundamentally broken. Relying on \"be careful\" human vigilance is a non-solution; developers need technical boundaries instead.\n\n**Key Points:** The article catalogs current attack vectors (fake CAPTCHAs, poisoned search ads, malicious `postinstall` scripts, prompt injection in AI coding tools) and traces real breaches",
